        "client_msg_id": "d9a47631-52d4-40b9-8dba-ea95f7b1f2f9",
        "text": "The other issue is sports strats are generally (not cricket) liquidity constrained not capital constrained. This means comparing a strat with a 10% edge or margin against one with a 1% edge means nothing without reference to the available liquidity that can be pushed through it, the margin comparison is only really useful if comparing two different versions of a similar strat operating in the same region of the same markets, i.e you are only going to choose one of them to run, so need to know which one is 'better'.",
